[1] Global as of 14 Dec 2021 - GPEI/WHO cVDPV2 (AFP Cote d'Ivoire, ES Guinea, Nigeris, Senegal)
Date: Thu 16 Dec 2021
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative/WHO
https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus Weekly Update 15 Dec 2021, World Health Organization
----------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 0
Environment: 0
Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 1
Environment: 15
Others: 1

Summary of new polioviruses this week:
- Côte d'Ivoire: 1 cVDPV2 case
- Guinea: 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample
- Nigeria: 12 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples
- Senegal: 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples

Afghanistan
- No new WPV1 or cVDPV2 viruses were reported this week. The total number of WPV1 cases in 2021 remains 4. The total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 43.

Pakistan
- No new WPV1 or cVDPV2 viruses were reported this week. The total number of WPV1 cases in 2021 remains 1. The total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 8.

Benin
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases reported in 2021. There were 3 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020. These cases are all linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.

Burkina Faso
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021. The country is affected by different outbreaks, 1 linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria and 1 to the Savanes outbreak in Togo.

Cameroon
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases reported in 2021.

Central African Republic
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Chad
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Congo
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Cote d'Ivoire
- One case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week in Loh-Djiboua, bringing the total number of cases in 2020 to 64. There are no reported cases in 2021.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 11 cases reported in 2021.

Egypt
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 10 positive samples reported in 2021.

Ethiopia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 9 cases reported in 2021.

Gambia
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 9 positive samples reported in 2021.

Ghana
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Guinea
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 6 cases in 2021.
- 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week in Conakry.

Guinea-Bissau
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases in the country which are linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria in 2021.

Kenya
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There was 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample reported in 2021. The virus is linked to the Banadir outbreak in Somalia.

Liberia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cVDPV2 cases in the country in 2021.

Madagascar
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. There are 10 cases reported in 2021.

Mali
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. No cases have been reported in 2021.

Mauritania
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 5 positive samples linked to the Jigawa outbreak in 2021.

Niger
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains 5.

Nigeria
- Twelve new cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported this week, from Borno, Kano, Katsina, Jigawa and Yobe. In 2021, 307 cases of cVDPV2 have been reported, along with 188 positive environmental samples.

Senegal
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 16 cases reported in 2021
- Two cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported this week in Dakar.

Sierra Leone
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 5 cases in 2021.

Somalia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 cVDPV2 case reported in 2021.

South Sudan
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 9 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2021.

Sudan
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. No cases have been reported in 2021.

Tajikistan
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 32 cases reported in 2021.

Togo
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. No cases have been reported in 2021.

Uganda
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 2 positive samples linked to the N'Djamena outbreak in Chad reported in 2021.

Ukraine
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2021.

Yemen
- No cases were reported in the past week. In 2021, 5 cases have been reported: 3 cVDPV1 and 2 cVDPV2.

Officially reported WPV1 and cVDPV cases as of 14 December 2021
Wild poliovirus (WPV)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2021: 5 (compared with 138 for the same period in 2020)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2020: 140

Circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus (cVDPV) cases
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2021: 484 [see Mod comment below] (compared with 809 for the same period in 2020)
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2020: 1113

